## Vectors in R {#vectors-in-r}

The most basic form of an R object is a vector. In fact, individual (scalar) values are vectors of length one.

We can concatenate values into a vector with `c()`.

```{R  }
# numeric vector
nums = c(1.1, 3, -5.7)
devs = rnorm(5)
devs
# logical vector
bools = c(TRUE, FALSE, TRUE)
bools
```


